/* Java Program to Remove a Character at a Specific Index *\

public class RemoveCharacter {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "Java Programming";
        int indexToRemove = 4; // The index of the character to remove
        
        // Remove character at the specified index
        String result = input.substring(0, indexToRemove) + input.substring(indexToRemove + 1);

        System.out.println("Original String: " + input);
        System.out.println("String after removing character at index " + indexToRemove + ": " + result);
    }
}
Output:
Original String: Java Programming
String after removing character at index 4: Java rogramming

Explanation:
input.substring(0, indexToRemove) gets the part of the string before the character to remove.
input.substring(indexToRemove + 1) gets the part of the string after the character to remove.
The two parts are concatenated, effectively removing the character at the specified index.
Example (Removing character at index 4):
If the input string is "Java Programming", and we remove the character at index 4 ('P').
